+### Failure modes (per tick)
 
 | Condition                                                          | Behavior |
 |---|---|
-| CDC event arrives before `phase:started`                           | Silently skipped; the catch-up scan reprocesses the writ post-seal. |
-| Dedupe lookup short-circuits on the same `(writId, writUpdatedAt)` | No `evaluate` call, no row, no transition. |
-| `validateConfig` throws                                            | Fail-loud log via the `[reckoner] scheduler:` prefix; evaluation is skipped (no row, no transition). |
-| `evaluate` throws or does not return an array                      | Fail-loud log; evaluation skipped. |
-| Decision carries a `writId` not in the candidate set               | Per-decision `console.warn` naming the offending id; ignore-and-continue. |
-| Two decisions target the same `writId`                             | Fail-loud log; the entire evaluation is skipped (no decision is applied). |
-| Decision carries an unknown outcome                                | Fail-loud log; the decision is ignored. |
+| Tick fires before `phase:started`                                  | Fail-loud throw at handler entry — `[reckoner] tick: activeScheduler not resolved — phase:started has not fired`. Production never trips this; misordered test fixtures get a deterministic loud signal. |
+| Held-petitions query returns an empty candidate set                | Early-return after the find. No `evaluate` call, no rows, no errors. |
+| Dedupe lookup short-circuits on the same `(writId, writUpdatedAt)` | The writ is dropped from the candidate set before `SchedulerInput` is built. No `evaluate` call for that writ; no row, no transition. |
+| Source disabled (`reckoner.disabledSources`)                       | Inline pre-scheduler decline: writ transitions to its cancelled target carrying a structured resolution; the row carries `declineReason: 'source_banned'` and the source in `remediationHint`. |
+| Source unregistered with `enforceRegistration: true`               | Inline pre-scheduler decline: writ transitions to its cancelled target carrying the legacy resolution string; the row carries `declineReason: 'source_unregistered'`. |
+| `validateConfig` throws                                            | Fail-loud log via the `[reckoner] scheduler:` prefix; **the entire tick is skipped** — no rows for any writ in this tick. |
+| `evaluate` throws or does not return an array                      | Fail-loud log; the entire tick is skipped. |
+| Decision carries a `writId` not in the candidate set               | Per-decision `console.warn` naming the offending id; ignore-and-continue. In-scope decisions still apply. |
+| Two decisions target the same `writId`                             | Fail-loud log; the entire tick is skipped — no decision is applied for any writ. |
+| Decision carries an unknown outcome                                | Fail-loud log; that decision is ignored, sibling decisions still apply. |
+
+### Tick relay
+
+The `reckoner.tick` relay and its `@every 60s` standing order live
+alongside the scheduler infrastructure. The relay is contributed
+through `apparatus.supportKit.relays`; the standing order through
+`apparatus.supportKit.standingOrders`. The relay's handler walks
+every currently-held petition (writs in `new` carrying
+`ext.reckoner`) on each fire, applies the source / disabled gates
+inline, dedupes against the Reckonings book, and hands the surviving
+candidate set to the active scheduler in **one batch** via a single
+`SchedulerInput`. Per-fire sequence:
+
+1. Resolve the active scheduler. Fail-loud throw if unresolved (D8).
+2. Query held petitions through the writs book.
+3. Apply source / disabled gates. Failing writs produce decline rows
+   and are dropped from the candidate set.
+4. Drop already-considered writs (dedupe on
+   `(writId, writUpdatedAt)`).
+5. Re-read and `validateConfig` the scheduler config; on throw,
+   log fail-loud and skip the whole tick.
+6. Call `evaluate` with the remaining candidates. On throw or
+   multi-decision per writ, log fail-loud and skip the whole tick.
+7. Apply each decision (transition + row) per the outcome mapping
+   above.
+
+`tickEventId` on each Reckonings row is stamped from the triggering
+`clockworks.timer` event id (D6). Test-only invocations through the
+in-package `runTick(event?: GuildEvent | null)` hook may pass `null`,
+in which case the field is omitted.
 
